local_schema.short_desc: A pair of string values that tell the D-Bus service name of the currently active location daemon and the location method used within that daemon
local_schema.longdesc: A pair of string values that tell the D-Bus service name of the currently active location daemon and the location method used within that daemon. For BlueTooth devices the location method is the address of the BlueTooth device. For integrated GPS and cellular network –based location the location method is always las. The default value is (com.nokia.Location, las). Examples: Integrated GPS and cellular: (com.nokia.Location, las) BlueTooth GPS: (org.freedesktop.Gypsy, 00:0D:B5:34:52:F6)

local_schema.short_desc: A boolean value that tells whether the user has accepted the location disclaimer or not
local_schema.longdesc: A boolean value that tells whether the user has accepted the location disclaimer or not. The default value is false, i.e., the user has not accepted the disclaimer. Until the user accepts the disclaimer the device shows the disclaimer dialog whenever an application tries to get location data through the location-*.h API. When set to true, the device doesn’t show the dialog any more.

local_schema.short_desc: A boolean value that tells whether the network-based methods are is disabled or enabled
local_schema.longdesc: A boolean value that tells whether the network-based methods are is disabled or enabled. The default value is false, i.e., network-based methods are enabled. This setting enables both AGPS and cellular network –based positioning. If the value of both gps_disabled and network_disabled are set to true, the location-control.h API method location_gpsd_control_start causes the enable dialog to be shown. If the user decides to enable network in the dialog, network_disabled is set to false and the system behaves accordingly.

local_schema.short_desc: A boolean value that tells whether the gps receiver is disabled or enabled
local_schema.longdesc: A boolean value that tells whether the gps receiver is disabled or enabled. The default value is false, i.e., the gps receiver is enabled. If the value of both gps_disabled and network_disabled are set to true, the location-control.h API method location_gpsd_control_start causes the enable dialog to be shown. If the user decides to enable GPS in the dialog, gps_disabled is set to false and the system behaves accordingly.
